# Setup SonarQube

pygoat - https://devguide.owasp.org/en/07-training-education/01-vulnerable-apps/03-pygoat/

```
Generate a complete Markdown guide for setting up SonarQube with GitLab CI/CD and Visual Studio Code for a Python project. The guide should include:

1. Running SonarQube in Docker.
2. Generating a SonarQube token.
3. Adding the token as a GitLab CI/CD variable.
4. Example Python project structure (app.py).
5. `sonar-project.properties` configuration.
6. `.gitlab-ci.yml` configuration for SonarScanner.
7. Instructions for VS Code integration with SonarLint.
8. How to test the setup (push to GitLab, MR, see results in SonarQube).
9. Optional: Python unit test example for coverage reporting.

Pro
```
